<br>
Karma is a wonderful thing because as of this very moment I'm taking down names. There are a lot of people out there that will do some very classy things. They'll res you, buff you, give you stuff they don't need and they expect nothing in return but that you do the same thing for another person as and when you can.<br>
<br>
Then there are others who feel that because they have the niche market on certain needed spells they can charge a small fortune. I don't have that much mana as a paladin and more often then not I need it but if I ever see a corpse on the ground I send that person a tell.<br>
<br>
&quot;I only have a 75% res but if'm more then willing to cast it.&quot; It wipes almost my entire mana pool but I'll be doing the same thing every day I log in regardless of what my objectives are at that time.<br>
<br>
It sickens me when I hear people /ooc'ing Can I get a res please? and someone shouts &quot;Yeah...for 100pp I'll res you&quot;, or &quot;Casting KEI for 200pp&quot; Those are the people going on my list. Those are the people that wont get my help in any form, whether it be my 90% res when I get it or just a little help trying to find their way around a zone.<br>
<br>
It was stated in another thread that these people have the right to certain amounts of money because some spells cost large amounts of money. I wonder just how many people are making notes that their spell cost 15k and theyve already made double that in donations so they know when to stop charging.<br>
<br>
